<h3>Daily Maintenance Tasks</h3>
<p>1. <strong>Cleaning Filters and Drains</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Remove and clean filters and drains to prevent clogs.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Prevents water from backing up and ensures proper drainage.</p>
<p>2. <strong>Wiping Down Interior and Exterior</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Clean the interior and exterior surfaces of the dishwasher, including the door seals.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Prevents buildup of food particles, grease, and grime, which can cause mechanical issues
  and reduce efficiency.</p>
<p>3. <strong>Checking Spray Arms</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Inspect and clean spray arms to ensure they are free from debris and can rotate freely.
</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Ensures proper water distribution for effective cleaning.</p>
<p>4. <strong>Checking Chemical Levels</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Ensure detergent, rinse aid, and sanitizer levels are adequate.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Ensures optimal cleaning and sanitation performance.</p>
<h3>Weekly Maintenance Tasks</h3>
