<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Removes mineral deposits and buildup that can affect performance.</p>
<p>2. <strong>Inspecting Hoses and Connections</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Check hoses and connections for signs of wear, leaks, or damage.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Prevents water leaks and potential water damage.</p>
<p>3. <strong>Lubricating Moving Parts</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Lubricate hinges, latches, and other moving parts as recommended by the manufacturer.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Reduces wear and tear and ensures smooth operation.</p>
<h3>Monthly Maintenance Tasks</h3>
<p>1. <strong>Inspecting Electrical Components</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Check electrical connections and components for signs of wear or damage.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Prevents electrical failures and ensures safe operation.</p>
<p>2. <strong>Testing Temperature Settings</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Action</strong>: Verify that the water temperature settings are within the recommended range.</p>
<p> - <strong>Benefit</strong>: Ensures effective cleaning and sanitization.</p>
