<h3>Factors to Consider</h3>
<p>1. <strong>Age of the Dishwasher</strong>:</p>
<p> - <strong>Rule of Thumb</strong>: Commercial dishwashers typically last around 8-10 years. If your unit is
  approaching or exceeding this age range, replacement might be more cost-effective in the long run.</p>
<p> - <strong>Technology Advancements</strong>: Newer models often come with improved energy efficiency, better water
